# Project Instructions

## Tooling

- Always use `deno` for running tasks or installing dependencies, see `deno.json`
- Run check script before completing tasks (`deno task check`)

## Key Commands

- `deno task test` - Run all tests
- `deno task test src/path/test-name.ts` - Run a specific test
- `deno task check` - Run the checks script (types, linting, formatting, building)
- `deno task fix` - Fix formatting and linting issues
- `deno task dev` - Run the development server

## Development practices

- Never use `any` or `@ts-ignore` in TypeScript files
- Prefer functional programming patterns where applicable
